            "answer_text": "Let a and b be two numbers, such that, a>b If from twice the greater of the two numbers, 20 is subtracted, the result is the other number 2a-20 = b 2a-b= 20 \u2014\u2014(1) If from twice the smaller number, 5 is subtracted, the result is the first number 2b-5 = a 2b-a = 5 \u2014\u2014(2) Solving the simultaneous equations, Multiplying (1) by 2, and adding (2), 4a-2b+2b-a= 40+5 3a = 45 a = 15 b= 2x15\u201320 = 10 Ans: Largest number is 15 Upvote if you agree! ",
