            "answer_text": "Let numbers be x, y. (Assume x>y) If from twice the greater of 2 numbers 20 is subtracted then the result is other number, that means, 2x-20 = y \u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014 > (1 eq.) If from twice the smaller number 5 is subtracted then the result is first number , that means , 2y-5 = x \u2014\u2014\u2014- > (2eq.) Replace 1 eq. In 2eq. 2(2x-20)-5 = x 4x-40\u20135 = x 4x-45 = x 4x-x = 45 3x = 45 x = 15. The greatest number is 15. If you want smallest number then replace x value in eq.1 or eq.2. 2y-5 = x 2y = x+5 2y = 15+5 2y = 20 y = 10. ",
